    public class FluoConfiguration
extends org.apache.commons.configuration.CompositeConfiguration
    Configuration helper class for Fluo. FluoConfiguration extends CompositeConfiguration.

      • getReporterConfiguration

        public org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration getReporterConfiguration(String reporter)
        Parameters:
        reporter - The name of the reporter to get configuration for, i.e. console, jmx, graphite.
        Returns:
        A SubsetConfiguration using the prefix "io.fluo.metrics.reporter" with the reporter parameter appended. Any change made to subset will be reflected in this configuration, but with the prefix added.

      • getAppConfiguration

        public org.apache.commons.configuration.Configuration getAppConfiguration()
        Returns:
        A SubsetConfiguration using the prefix "io.fluo.app". Any change made to subset will be reflected in this configuration, but with the prefix added. This method is useful for setting application configuration before initialization. For reading application configuration after initialization, see FluoClient.getAppConfiguration()
